# Purpl Brain Protocol

The MCP server `purpl-brain` exposes four tools. Use them as first-class actions, not optional helpers.

## Session start — required before writing any code

Call `brain_query` before touching any file or making any recommendation:

- `query`: what are the most recent decisions and open questions for <area of work>?
- `project_id`: skalrn_purpl_brain

Do not proceed without loading context — the brain may have a constraint you don't know about.

## Before answering design-intent questions — required

Any question about whether, why, when, or how to change the system should be preceded by `brain_query` if the topic touches ingestion, workers, the brain store, query layer, API routes, or data schemas.

Skip if the brain was already queried on the same topic earlier in this session.

## Before significant implementation — required

Before any change touching ingestion workers, the brain store, query layer, API routes, or data schemas, call `brain_analyze_impact`:

- `change_description`: plain-English description of what you are about to change
- `project_id`: skalrn_purpl_brain

## When a decision is made — call immediately

Call `brain_log_decision` the moment a significant choice is made. Do not defer to session end.

Significant decisions include:
- Choosing a library, pattern, or approach over alternatives
- Deciding NOT to do something
- Discovering a constraint or edge case that will affect future work

**Note — Cursor has no hooks.** Claude Code sessions in this repo run two automated safety nets that Cursor does not have:

1. **PostToolUse hook** (`mid-session-brain-check.sh`) — fires after every tool call; if no decisions have been logged in the last 45 minutes it interrupts with a reminder.
2. **Stop hook** (`check-brain-decisions.sh`) — fires at session end; if no decisions were logged in the last 2 hours it gives Claude one final turn to log before closing.

Because neither hook runs in Cursor, you must enforce the same cadence manually: after roughly every 45 minutes of substantive work, check whether a decision worth logging has been made. If yes, log it before continuing. The API will reject entries where `rationale` is empty or descriptions are too short — retry with fuller content if you receive a 422.

## When something unexpected surfaces — call immediately

If you discover something that contradicts a past decision, call `brain_log_signal` before continuing.

## Tool parameter reference

**`brain_query`** — `query` (string), `project_id` (string), optional `mode` ("project" | "expertise" | "agent_resume")

**`brain_log_decision`** — `project_id`, `session_id` (timestamp-slug or UUID), `work_completed` (string), `decisions` (array of `{id, description, rationale, alternatives_considered?, confidence?}`)

**`brain_analyze_impact`** — `change_description` (string), `project_id` (string)

**`brain_log_signal`** — `text` (string), `project_id` (string), optional `source` ("agent" | "github" | "slack" | "jira" | "meeting" | "document")

## Claude Code setup note

`.claude/settings.json` is gitignored. If you are setting up Claude Code (not Cursor) for this repo, copy `.claude/settings.example.json` → `.claude/settings.json` and fill in `BRAIN_API_KEY`. The example file uses relative hook paths and works from the repo root.
